# Call Sheet JSON Format (Canonical)

When parsing call sheets into JSON, **always** use this exact structure. See `docs/CALL_SHEET_JSON_FORMAT.md` for full spec.

```json
{
  "source_file": "Production Name M:D:YY.pdf",
  "production_info": {
    "production_name": "Production Name",
    "date": "Month DD, YYYY",
    "company_name": "Company Name (optional)"
  },
  "crew_size": 11,
  "crew": [
    {"name": "...", "role": "...", "department": "...", "phone": "...", "email": "..."}
  ]
}
```

- When crew identities exist: include `crew_size` (tally of crew.length) and `crew` array.
- When call sheet has NO crew identity information: omit `crew_size`, use `crew: []`. Blank CREW SIZE on leaderboard is valid.
- `production_info.date` = Job Date when known (e.g. "June 10, 2025"); omit if unknown.
- `crew` = one object per person (name, role, department, phone, email), or [] when no names listed.
